    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "therapists dont understand... they just see a patient. they dont see the way my daughter sighs when she has to help me into the bath, or how my son looks when he's checking his watch while i'm talking. it's not just ups and downs. it's the weight of it all. i've lived a long life, i've done my part. i just... i wonder if it would be more peaceful for everyone if i wasn't so much of a weight around their necks.",
